    "updated_at": "2013-02-28T20:21:07Z",
    "body": "Yeah, I concur with @lifthrasiir , we allow mixed-case hex literals too. There are unfortunately quite a few ways to write numerically-equal numbers. This doesn't strike me as a big deal either way, I was just going with the most common grammars for FP out there. http://rosettacode.org/wiki/Literals/Floating_point\n",
